<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36091c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36091c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36091c"> 91(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pitching</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The paving of the city was not seriously taken in hand till 1773, when an act was passed for a general pavement of the streets of Dublin. The system adopted was that known as &ldquo;<mark>pitching</mark>&rdquo;, or the use of small round boulder stones <font color="green">[cobblestones]</font>, remains of which are yet to be traced in back thoroughfares. <small> Samuel A. Ossory Fitzpatrick, <a name="SAOF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SAOF"><cite title="source">Dublin: A Historical and Topographical Account of the City</cite></a> (1907) 197</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
